@NODE Intro
@TITLE "Introduction to Topicdemo.amirx"

@{U}So, why do Topicdemo.amirx?@{UU}

Well, I've been an IRC user for ooh about 7 months now, and I've seen so
many good topics that it's unbelieveable ;)  I got sick and tired of calling
one from memory all the time that I've been bored in a channel, so I decided
to write a script which would randomly call a topic.

This script will, once run, randomly put a topic onto the channel that you
are currently on.  At the moment, it is very limited.  I am working on
making the topics user configarable.

@{U}What's the difference between Topicdemo.amirx and Topic.amirx?@{UU}

Well, Topicdemo.amirx ( the file you now have ) has a limited number of
topics.  Topic.amirx has a lot more topics, and doesn't have the annoying
message preceeding the topic change ;-)

@ENDNODE

