@NODE Install
@TITLE "Installation of this script"

Installation of this script is really easy.

All you have to do is:

   -  Get the file Topicdemo.amirx
   -  Copy it to Amirc:rexx
   -  Assign Amirc: if you haven't already done so ;)
   -  Eg Assign AmIRC: Data:AmIRC

OK?

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage
@TITLE "Usage of this lovely piece of ARexx"

To use this script is very easy.

All you need to do is either :

1)  Select the script from the REXX menu on AmIRC
2)  Type /rx topicdemo

***TIP***

Why not try using an alias?

I use /t to put a new topic to the channel.

@{u}How do I set an alias then? @{uu}

All you need to so is type:

/alias t topicdemo.amirx %p

That will enable you to randomly select a topic by only typing /t

Cool eh? ;-)

@ENDNODE

